;(First interaction)
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502019101: Config/Level/NPCDialogue/P10202/F10202001_G43/Act/Act_502019101.json-->
::'''Wu He:''' ...If everyone thought like you did, the art of Butterfly Immersia would be wiped out! If master Zi Run had listened to these so-called "business interests" back then, "The Bridge to Grandma's Home" would've never even been released!
::'''Nanjie:''' Ha, then you can take your artistic dreams and your bridge &mdash; and jump off it into a lake! Do you think I said this to cause you pain? Why can't we all make a little money together? Why have you gotta be so pig-headed...
::'''Wu He:''' But... Art cannot be measured by commercial impact alone! Why would you try to make a living in this industry if you have no respect for art at all?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Fight! Fight!
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502019105-->
:::'''Wu He:''' ...And who are you? Egging us on to fight like this... What can you get out of this?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You two: Quit arguing!
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502019108-->
:::'''Wu He:''' Oh, I... I'm really sorry about that. We kind of went a bit goblin mode there and should've paid more attention to our surroundings.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You guys wait here. I'll go find the Realm-Keeping Commission.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502019111-->
:::'''Wu He:''' No no no, please don't bother the Realm-Keeping Commission with this little tiff of ours.
::'''Nanjie:''' *sigh* Wu He, calm down. Let's not put on a show for people.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502019113-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502019113-->
::'''Wu He:''' I'm arguing with you out of creative license, right... Let me explain to the {{MC|f=girl|m=boy}} here &mdash; we're Butterfly Immersia creatives. She's Nanjie, the producer &mdash; and I'm the director, Wu He.
::'''Nanjie:''' Let's stop there, for you to get calmed down. Sorry to make you laugh. Have you got anything you'd like to say?
;(Subsequent interactions)
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502019102: Config/Level/NPCDialogue/P10202/F10202001_G43/Act/Act_502019102.json-->
::'''Wu He:''' ...Modern media breaks down, pulverizes, and distills every soul capable of aesthetic beauty into a "creative assembly line" &mdash; then has the cheek to turn around and tell us "The creative assembly line doesn't need any more creativity"!
::'''Nanjie:''' But whoever has the resources to create art also has the right to create art... Uh... Hold on a minute... Are you looking for us? What's up?
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
